author: James Massola
title: George Christensen resigns as Nationals whip
text:
Surfer Kelly Slater calls for a shark cull Surfer Kelly Slater calls for a shark cull 
Reunion Island has had 20 shark attacks since 2011, and the surfing great has called for a "serious" cull, but he's been met with opposition. More videos Is George going rogue? 
Nationals MP George Christensen reportedly has a resignation letter penned that, if he hands in, will cause all sorts of trouble for the government. 
Mr Christensen, however, has a been a frequent and vocal critic of the Turnbull government on a range of policy issues and has repeatedly threatened to cross the floor and back Labor's proposal for a royal commission into the banking sector. 
He has dismissed suggestions he could defect from the Liberal National Party and join Pauline Hanson's One Nation, claiming he is personally loyal to Deputy Prime Minister Barnaby Joyce. He has, however, threatened to resign from the LNP. SHARE
